flowRoot.flowPara: Strip on the left opens the app picker. Strip on the right indicates the current workspace and allows workspace switching/creation/removal.
Visually this state looks like it belongs to the regular session - the background doesn't change.
In contrast to the window picker, this is another "place" - visually it is either a new view or a new element that has obscured the session.

The first grid of launchers are the user's favorites. Apps can be added and removed as well as rearranged. Folders can be created using drag and drop. There's no upper limit on the number of favorites and they can span multiple pages.
If there are multiple pages of favorites, it's hard to ensure that the suggested apps don't repeat them. Possibilities:
- show the suggestions at the top of all applications
